                            <h1 class="display-4 mb-4"><br>About David</h1>
                            <p class="mb-4">A Sacramentan since 1985, I parented three children who attended public schools. I made my living as a newspaper editor/writer and a Legal Aid attorney, helping seniors. I have worked on federal cases defending free speech and engaged in political action for international human rights and social justice in our community. Since 2015, I have served as an elected Democratic Central Committee member, working to promote responsiveness to public concerns.
                            </p>
                            <p class="my-4">Congress has not addressed the needs and dreams of voters in the region. I join the large majorities in demanding: reversing of global warming; environmental protection; reproductive rights; gender and racial justice; affordable housing; accessible education; living wages; and universal healthcare through passage of Expanded/Improved Medicare for All.
                            </p>
                            <p class="mb-4">These social priorities are undermined by our current U.S. foreign policies championed by too many in Congress. Reducing our massive military spending is critical for funding efforts that enhance community well-being. Eliminating war as an option is essential to protecting the planet and human life.
                            </p>
							<p ><br></p>
							
